content.introduction: Welcome to your personalized nutrigenomics report. This document provides insights into how your genes influence your diet, nutrition, and overall health.
content.genomicsExplanation: Genomics is the study of an organism's complete set of DNA, including all of its genes. It helps us understand how genetic variations can impact various biological processes.
content.genesHealthImpact: Your genes play a significant role in determining your health predispositions. This report highlights key genetic markers and their potential impact on your well-being.
content.fundamentalsPRS: Polygenic Risk Scores (PRS) combine the effects of many genetic variants to estimate an individual's risk for complex diseases or traits.
content.utilityDoctors: This report is designed to be a valuable tool for doctors and dietitians, providing actionable genetic insights to personalize patient care and recommendations.
content.microarrayExplanation: Microarray technology allows for the simultaneous measurement of the expression levels of thousands of genes, providing a comprehensive genetic profile.
content.microarrayData: Your microarray data has been analyzed to identify specific genetic variations relevant to your health and lifestyle.
